ce:section.ce:para:
Active species such as holes (h
+
), superoxide radicals ( ⋅ O
2 −
), and hydroxyl radicals ( ⋅ OH) may be factors that affect photocatalytic denitrification. It is important to quantify and capture the main active species produced by the C/M-10 composite. In this work, EDTA-2Na and tert-butanol (TBA) were chosen as scavengers for holes (h
+
) and hydroxyl radicals ( ⋅ OH). P-benzoquinone (BQ) and N2 were used as scavengers of superoxide radicals ( ⋅ O
2 −
). As shown in Fig. 8, the TBA (1 mL) has little effect on C/M-10 photocatalytic removal of NO. The addition of 0.5 mmol EDTA-2Na has a significant inhibitory effect on the photocatalytic activity of C/M-10. The addition of BQ (0.5 mmol) and N2 also has a certain inhibitory effect on the photocatalytic activity. It can be concluded that the active species such as h
+
and ⋅ O
2 −
play a vital role in the photo-denitrification process.
